#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:1
msgid "Autotools package"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:3
msgid ""
"An Autotools package provides support for processing a [GNU Build System"
"][gnu-build-sys] supported module."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:10
msgid ""
"The following shows the default arguments used in stages and outlines "
"configuration options that are available for an Autotools package to set."
" See also the [Autotools package examples](/examples/examples-autotools)."
" All stages are invoked with a [`PKG_BUILD_DIR`](env-pkg-build-dir) "
"working directory."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:21
msgid "Configuration stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:24
msgid "The configuration stage will invoke `./configure` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:30
msgid "The prefix arguments are configured to [`LIBFOO_PREFIX`](pkg-opt-prefix)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:32
msgid ""
"If [`LIBFOO_AUTOTOOLS_AUTORECONF`](pkg-opt-autotools-autoreconf) is "
"configured, `autoreconf` will be invoked before `./configure` is started:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:45
msgid "Build stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:48
msgid "The build stage invokes `make` with the arguments:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:54
msgid ""
"The number of jobs is populated by either the [`--jobs` argument](arg-"
"jobs), [`LIBFOO_FIXED_JOBS`](pkg-opt-fixed-jobs) or [`LIBFOO_MAX_JOBS"
"`](pkg-opt-max-jobs). Although, if the configuration results in a single "
"job, the argument will not be used."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:65
msgid "Install stage"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:68
msgid "The install stage invokes `make` with an `install` target:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:74
msgid "With the following environment variables set:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:80
msgid ""
"The `DESTDIR` path will be set to the target sysroot the package should "
"install into (see also [`LIBFOO_INSTALL_TYPE`](pkg-opt-install-type)). "
"`make install` may be invoked multiple times for each target it needs to "
"install into."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:85
msgid ""
"If a package defines install options, the `install` target is not "
"provided by default."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:90
msgid "`LIBFOO_AUTOTOOLS_AUTORECONF`"
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/guides/packages/pkg-type-autotools.md:92
msgid ""
"Specifies whether the package needs to perform an Autotools re-"
"configuration. This is to assist in the rebuilding of GNU Build System "
"files which may be broken or a patch has introduced new build script "
"changes that need to be applied. This field is optional. By default, "
"`autoreconf` is not invoked."
msgstr ""

